sec.p:
The neurological manifestations linked to these symptoms involve the development of “tangles” and “plaque” composed of a detrimental protein known as Amyloid Beta (A

    β

). The entorhinal cortex and hippocampus are where pathological neurofibrillary tangles gradually build up. These are the regions of the brain responsible for both immediate and enduring memory in individuals [23]. Neuroscientists have shown that maintaining communication between these two brain regions is crucial for preserving memory. Any disruption in this connection can interrupt the circuit and result in memory disturbance, ultimately leading to memory loss [24].
